<p>&nbsp;Supporters can help financially in various ways. One of the simplest is by practicing responsible social media behavior and reporting incidents of cyber aggression when witnessed. People can reach out to political representatives, report abuse directly to platforms, join the HONR Forum to assist with content removal, or use HONR’s online reporting tool to alert the organization to harmful material. Additionally, supporters can contribute by purchasing HONR apparel from the organization’s shop.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The HONR Network relies on the commitment of volunteers and donors. Professionals with relevant expertise can offer their services to victims, while others can volunteer to identify and remove hate content through HONR’s private forum or volunteer forms. Donations of any size help fund the organization’s programs, advocacy, and educational initiatives aimed at protecting survivors and families while building a safer online environment for everyone.</p>
